text: Tate McRae has announced a massive 2025 tour, dubbed the “Miss Possessive Tour.” The trek comes in support of her third studio album, So Close to What, which is set to arrive on February 21st via RCA Records. The 60-date stretch will initially take the dancer and singer to South America for appearances at Lollapalooza Argentina, Chile, and Brazil; she’ll then head to Europe and the UK before touching back down for a full stretch of North American concerts in summer 2025. How Can I Get Tickets to Tate McRae’s “Miss Possessive Tour?” Tickets to a major of Tate McRae’s “Miss Possessive Tour” are already sold out. However, fans can still  look for deals or get tickets to sold-out shows via StubHub, where orders are 100% guaranteed through StubHub’s FanProtect program. Tate McRae’s “Miss Possessive Tour”  kicks off on March 18th in Mexico City, with shows to follow in cities like São Paulo, London, Paris, Amsterdam, Prague, Vancouver, New York, Austin, Nashville, and many more. The 2025 trek is set to wrap up in Los Angeles at the Kia Forum on September 27th. html:
Tate McRae has announced a massive 2025 tour, dubbed the “Miss Possessive Tour.” The trek comes in support of her third studio album, So Close to What, which is set to arrive on February 21st via RCA Records.

The 60-date stretch will initially take the dancer and singer to South America for appearances at Lollapalooza Argentina, Chile, and Brazil; she’ll then head to Europe and the UK before touching back down for a full stretch of North American concerts in summer 2025.

Get Tate McRae Tickets Here

Get tickets here, and scroll below for more details on how to experience her high-energy choreography in person.

How Can I Get Tickets to Tate McRae’s “Miss Possessive Tour?”

Tickets to a major of Tate McRae’s “Miss Possessive Tour” are already sold out. However, fans can still  look for deals or get tickets to sold-out shows via StubHub, where orders are 100% guaranteed through StubHub’s FanProtect program. StubHub is a secondary market ticketing platform, and prices may be higher or lower than face value, depending on demand.

What Is Tate McRae’s “Miss Possessive Tour”?

Tate McRae’s “Miss Possessive Tour”  kicks off on March 18th in Mexico City, with shows to follow in cities like São Paulo, London, Paris, Amsterdam, Prague, Vancouver, New York, Austin, Nashville, and many more. The 2025 trek is set to wrap up in Los Angeles at the Kia Forum on September 27th.

The “Miss Possessive Tour” will be Tate McRae’s third headlining outing; her first headlining tour took place in 2022 and was followed by a 2023 trek, bolstered by the success of singles like “greedy” and “exes.” Known for her strong dance background, McRae will spend her 2025 tour performing cuts from her forthcoming third LP, So Close to What, which she recently teased with the single “2 hands.”

Who Is Opening for Tate McRae on Tour?

Pop artist Zara Larsson will be along as a special guest for the US and Canada dates. New Zealand-born singer-songwriter BENEE, who broke out with her 2020 hit “Supalonely,” is joining for the shows in Europe and the UK.

What Are Tate McRae 2025 Tour Dates?

See the full list of Tate McRae’s upcoming tour dates below, including her appearances at the annual KIIS FM “Jingle Ball” taking place in December. Score tickets to the “Miss Possessive Tour” here.
